  "description": "Gourd/squash/melon family — 95 genera, ~965 species. Diagnostic tendril-bearing vines, unisexual flowers, inferior ovary developing into pepo fruit, cucurbitacins (bitter triterpenes) defense. Ancient and widespread domestication; among the highest-ranking families for human food plants.",
